					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Hard work does pay....</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Conviction</a> | 
		            4/23/2002 1:20:17 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Money makes the world go around. I list here some information which I hope will be helpful to others. We al lwant better items for our characters, some just for the status others out of need. Well here are some tips, first of all what not to do.<BR>
<BR>
Donts:<BR>
<BR>
1. Begging, this will not earn you any friends that much is for sure. Alot of low levels seem to think that by pestering high levels for coin and items they will get stuff,WRONG. All you do is make alot of enemies and a bad name for yourself.<BR>
<BR>
2. Do not rip people of when you are selling items. I have seen first hand this happening, price hikes and out right lies to get items. People will talk and remeber your name and soon noone respectable will buy or sell with you.<BR>
<BR>
3. See above two points, read-reread-then read again.<BR>
<BR>
  You will find that just being honest and helping others will find you a wealth of friends and coin. It has been my experince that if people see you trying and working hard to earn stuff, they are more inclined to help you achive your ends.<BR>
  Ok some basic good things now.....<BR>
<BR>
Do:<BR>
<BR>
1. Treat others as you want to be treated.<BR>
<BR>
2. If someone is in trouble offer to help. Not only is this a good way to make friends but also makes you feel good about yourself(yea yea ewe).<BR>
<BR>
3. Try to be honest when selling, I know we dont always know all the prices but try to find a reasonable price to agree upon. This way both parties walk away happy.<BR>
<BR>
4. Remeber JUST A GAME!! Have fun explore, make new friends, HAVE FUN!!<BR>
<BR>
 Ok now that all of the basics covered lets make some coin. Below I will list couple of known ways to earn coin, WITHOUT BEGGING!<BR>
<BR>
THE BEARS:<BR>
<BR>
 Yes all druid please look away :p. One of the best ways to earn quick coin is killing bears. People will always be looking to buy pelts, you can get as much as 40pp per HQ(High Quality) bear skins. Now the prices may vary but either way good fast coin. I have found the best place to do this is Halaas, and its not the only place but the best I have found so far. Dont forget that taylors will buy all types of pelts but HQbear bring the best coin(unless you super lucky and bag a excellent quality which I have only ever seen one in my full year of playing EQ). <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Payback and Pleasure:<BR>
<BR>
 This way takes longer but when you think about it every little coin helps. Go to camps or areas you know you can kill the mobs easy and just start killing. Loot everything you can and sell. This is time consuming and can be very boring at times, but is a surefire way to rake in coin at a good steady pace. Word of advice though, if lower levels are around its probably better not to camp like say(orcs in ec or other such camps during prime time) This detracts from other players of lower levels chances for leveling and plain old fun.<BR>
<BR>
The Tunnel(East Commons):<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
 By far I would have to say this is the best and fastest way to earn coin. I did this for a week and raked in over 7k. Ok first to clear up no scamming or cheating involed just good old fashion work.<BR>
 Ok save up about 100pp(maybe by using one of the above listed suggestions) and head to East Commons mainly the tunnel there. This is well known on alot of servers as the Bazaar(well before Luclin came out and most likely till they get the Bazaar working :p). Anyway the key to this money making skill is be calm and no rushing time is on your side. I have found if you watch the auctions that over time people become tired of standing around and just want to go level or explore more(this is your time). At this point people will dump items for lower prices just to get rid of them. Plain and simple by something cheap say example: Centi Shortsword someone sells you one for 300pp, well now you turn around and sell for 500pp. The main key is dont be in a hurry just wait(its good if you learn how to bind keys, saves you alot of time typing). Sooner or later someone will want the item you have and will pay what you ask as long as you arent price hiking. I would suggest watch auctions for a day or two and see what moves alot and what doesnt. Thats it easy huh? I am sure over time you can devise your own way to do little differnces thats part of the fun. Please though just remeber do not screw over your fellow players its bad for business.<BR>
  Example: When I see something I know can move fast I will send the person a tell. Say the have a Bloodstained mantle for 200pp, I would offer them 100pp(now pay attention) I would offer them, do not lie to people and say item is only worth so and so just to buy cheap. If you offer a price and the agree then they see you selling the cheaply bought item or items for more they cant really say anything because you did not force them to sell to you nor did you lie about real worth in order to gain. Remeber have fun earn coin but dont take away from others fun.<BR>
<BR>
 Ok well ther you have it couple of things that may or may not help.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Besafe! Enjoy this fun filled game!<BR>
<BR>
Conviction Pally of the 13th Season<BR>
Proud member of Clan Loreweaver(Rathe Server)
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
